-7 + 3t &= -5 + 4u \\
0 &= \tfrac{4}{3} + \tfrac{u}{3}
\end{align*}
\end{answer}

We now make \(u\) the unknown variable by solving the third equation for \(u\). <answer> <align*>
u &= -4 \\
4 - 3t &= -2 + 2(-4) \\
-7 + 3t &= -5 + 4(-4) \\
0 &= \tfrac{4}{3} + \tfrac{-4}{3} \\
